Package nusri.fyp.demo.roboflow.request

Enum Class RoboflowRequest

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<RoboflowRequest>
nusri.fyp.demo.roboflow.request.RoboflowRequest
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<RoboflowRequest>, Constable
public enum RoboflowRequest extends Enum<RoboflowRequest>
Enum representing various Roboflow API requests. Each enum constant corresponds to a specific API endpoint with its associated HTTP method, URI, success and failure response types, and request body type.

    • buildUriWithPathVars

      private URI buildUriWithPathVars(String uriTemplate, Map<String,String> pathVar) throws URISyntaxException
      Builds a URI by replacing path variables in the given URI template with the corresponding values in the provided map. If there are any unprocessed placeholders like "{*}", an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.
      Parameters:
      uriTemplate - the URI template containing placeholders
      pathVar - a map of path variables to replace placeholders in the URI template
      Returns:
      the constructed URI with replaced path variables
      Throws:
      URISyntaxException - if the URI template is invalid or contains unprocessed placeholders
      IllegalArgumentException - if the URI template contains unprocessed placeholders (e.g., "{*}")
